{"_id":"0aDXZBWHVz6xF9Yi","name":"Divine Lore of Nippon","content":"<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Orange Simca</h2>\n<p>The Orange Simca is the Goddess of the Rising Sun, Honor and War. Her followers consist primarily of the warrior clans that dominate Nippon (although many commoners worship her for protection and strength), with the warrior monks being the most fanatical of her worshippers. She is often paid tribute in silver, blooming flowers, snake bones and silks. It is said her worshippers feel a greater sense pride and vigor when basking in the sun but are somewhat melancholy and composed during the night. The monks are said to be so blessed or inspired by her holy light that they don&rsquo;t need to sleep, defending the innocent as their goddess rests in the heavens until the next morning.</p>\n<h3><strong>Orange Simca's Blessings and Strictures :</strong></h3>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.ElmLfnrXliStS9CP]{Battle}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.Cg2Q3TV66cpmheHS]{Blessing of Courage}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.52846%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.iIfYOlNrLb0uiV8c]{Fortune}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 23.6365%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.0r3moMIHXsBrcOyh]{Blessing of Hardiness}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.815%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.KSDrXcieyRc37YI7]{Blessing of Might}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.2WN0muIB2BFd4kBO]{Blessing of Righteousness}</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li>Do not watch the sun as it sets but be prepared to see as it rises. Guard the innocent as she sleeps.</li>\n<li>Always ask three times for permission before accepting any gifts from the innocent, as it is a warrior&rsquo;s duty to protect the helpless, not to take from them.</li>\n<li>Always offer aid to warriors against Skaven who ask for it, regardless of political affiliation or race.</li>\n<li>Offer sacrifices on the first morning of every month, as tribute for a new month of light.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Miracles of the Orange Simca</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.7VFt6NvQDaTa3T4w]{Banzai Charge}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.dju9rslGfI84KHLi]{Beacon of Sacred Might}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.QsIrJbq7R05zOvRT]{Bushido's Call}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.NDgYm2aVCMj10VK8]{Gift of the Rising Sun}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.GbuVXGEqtWWhHGNO]{Red Sun's Smite}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.emnvQoIdxTSGCY1B]{Serpent's Eye}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.XVCxX1BwEPMMiKwm]{Shield of the Sun}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.oqjygKIczvH6zA1j]{Sunfire}</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.J5KbKT2hDGt2SAmY"}}}
{"_id":"1UmVZK18Zs4YUm4K","name":"Nations of Mankind Bestiary","content":"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>I. Mounts</strong></h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>II. Empire Bestiary</strong></h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>III. Bretonnia Bestiary</strong></h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>IV. Dog of War Bestiary</strong></h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>V. Kislev Bestiary</strong></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Mounts</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.Ws11CG2ZaQgjtXL5]{Bretonnian Destrier}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.O7WMkJcCYM0CaTcI]{Demigryph War Mount}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.fELjTU1CJxVFFikT]{Hippogryph Mount}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.RN35DlsFXk8laiij]{Imperial Griffon Mount}</li>\n<li>&nbsp;@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.y2nTZSqIiXJlwrWS]{Kislev Light Warhorse}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.kp3yCVC6OHNYQsHh]{Kislev Warbear}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.x5sOHB1mjEM8NJzq]{Light War Pegasus}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.NeM2E7D9SWFYtKkH]{Norscan Mammoth}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.8BL5lyYy9fSx5iBn]{Riding Camel}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.WAJ4ZNjzGoTXUYpl]{Royal Pegasus}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.9xKqNGmuZyVRSzj9]{War Camel}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.xTWZzYECL0TaBN1o]{War Elephant}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Empire Bestiary</h2>\n<p>Each regiment has a wide variety of weapons for certain types of engagements, with spears, halberds, and swords being the most common and the most flexible in battle situations. Imperial regiments used as long-range support are often equipped with handguns, crossbows, and longbows, among others. When not in war, Imperial soldiers are required to drill and train on a regular basis in order to build their stamina and deepen their martial abilities when the time for combat soon reappears. Supervised by drill-sergeants, these men and women are harshly instructed in the importance of formation tactics and the need to fight as a cohesive unit capable of lending support to one another in the chaos of the battlefield.</p>\n<p><strong>Optional: </strong>For an even more diverse roster and to add further customization options, GMs should consider including Human starting Talents based on the Empire Provinces the Imperials of this bestiary hail from. Consult the Regiments of Renown or Knightly Order Skills and Talents for further customization. For further variety, reduce the Attributes of a unit by 10 each and roll 2d10 to determine their stats.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Where march you, men of Reikland, where carry your halberd and sword... We march to war for our Emperor, and Sigmar our saviour and lord... Tomorrow we go to war, to face the hordes of Chaos... Tomorrow we will be buried, in cold graves that await us... And when the fighting is done, and the sun goes down at night... Hear my prayers, save my soul, and take me to Sigmar's Light...&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash;Old soldier's song from Reikland</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.ZAyA5yCorK30enbG]{Empire Swordsman}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.Gc8zm9RZL4Hp4RZE]{Empire Halberdier}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.GHnr17AgCES0P45m]{Empire Spearman}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.E5jsTMXdfZmudiHK]{Empire Handgunner}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.T8VMO1Gm6l1hlmQz]{Empire Archer}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.dHEfPyg0LaMnacy9]{Empire Crossbowman}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.j3DQrVBg8TeFFxLk]{Empire Greatswords}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.MWkQYon61yXu8zeA]{Empire Sergeant}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.P61l4OlQRdRaqHYR]{Empire Captain}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.h08C7QSyhC7sGCl7]{Empire General}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.qUNw0TE3bZtcxRbD]{Empire Pistolier}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.90NmbarJMu7btq2A]{Empire Outrider}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.pwFsKb71RU27re4Y]{War Priest of Sigmar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.fjGpxQsd5zgI9yCd]{War Priest Captain of Sigmar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.3SYojouHW5ibz4WU]{Arch-Lector of Sigmar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.qeQfr5T30VYqMGsH]{Empire Knight}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.RffwAS4FhDtiBv8B]{Empire Knight of the Inner Circle}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.itHnienoaLi5yS6I]{Empire Grand Master}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.3u43UebYIATKIRMJ]{Witch Hunter}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.sjDBtPnZN2Zeh0eU]{Witch Hunter General}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.kD1nFxieasKhA7Bu]{Empire Master Engineer}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.9zNm1QszxVRilyiq]{Empire Battle Wizard}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.8ARVg4Vmp1hu8CYa]{Magister Wizard Lord}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.iio77BUIQiRlsDZK]{Magister Patriarch}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.OA64owKq3O6zsluw]{Flagellant}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.fNDhw2zhF7XGxRm1]{Prophet of Doom}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.FlZNjAPchhai8eeT]{War Priest of Ulric}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.2b256IohnfVYM23T]{War Priest Captain of Ulric}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.ttxw1wM9UsmdhNTy]{Arch-Lector of Ulric}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.QFTzfab3FZDSCwhG]{Free Company Militia}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.LHj8nLkMJRusKRP5]{Free Company Leader}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Bretonnia Bestiary</h2>\n<p>The Bretonnian military are a powerful army formed around a core of brave knights supported by scores of low-born peasants. They are a warlike and valiant people who willingly seek out battles as a way of securing personal honor and pride. Any who invade their domains face the fury of their powerful knights and few foes can match them on open ground. The knights range from the youngest Knights Errant, eager to prove their worth, through the Knights of the Realm, defenders of the land. Rarer still are the Questing Knights, wandering warriors engaged in a quest for the Grail. And then there are the legendary Grail Knights themselves, who have succeeded in their quest and sipped from their goddess's Grail, becoming imbued with fey power and longevity. Riding into war atop the finest steeds, from mighty Warhorses to soaring Pegasi and roaring Hippogryphs, the Knights of Bretonnia are warriors with few equals.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.uLzXWvpPh5y3NGZy]{Man-At-Arms}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.pOuWVoP5TsgZeARg]{Peasant Bowman}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.VFE6Gvwr6qqbCvNZ]{Yeoman}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.v9NcZiDovCZoo10g]{Yeoman Sergeant}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.vAVle82tdfZrQZP6]{Grail Pilgrim}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.wSd159S7LZm7ESmH]{Battle Pilgrim}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.ReIzMxwoeeYBscmk]{Foot Squire}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.dW1DjAGCdvDEXGUy]{Foot Knight}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.eMjmwyyKhCGuqevt]{Son of Bretonnia}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.eAYx7TpwNmzhAJut]{Knight Errant}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.udH8qJa8QF9cRznS]{Knight of the Realm}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.zE9L3qH3p8eL4SHK]{Questing Knight}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.7l6NijEv0CXP5hGV]{Grail Knight}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.SRDVs49raPJG9F94]{Paladin}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.4Re23oD3iOkvIfvw]{Bretonnian Lord}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.YIheuUmFYmJqvylU]{Grail Damsel}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.lD8obDilachGVnrF]{Prophetess of The Lady}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Dog of War Bestiary</h2>\n<p>The Dogs of War, also known as the Regiments of Renown, is a polite catch-all term to generally describe Mercenaries from all across the known World, fighting on behalf of anyone willing to pay their exorbitant prices. They are drawn to places where fortunes can be won by ruthless adventures. From the lush jungles of the West to the misty isles of the East, and from the steamy swamplands of the South to the harsh snowlands of the north, the world is truly awash with rag-tag armies of sellswords who nurture the wishful dreams of loot, plunder and adventure. Although many Dogs of War ply their bloody trade to every point on the compass, the most notorious breeding-ground of mercenaries lies within the fraction war-torn city-states of Tilea in the Old World. From all the kingdoms of the Old World and many more beyond, sell-swords come towards Tilea in the tens of thousands, reassured of profitable employment and great battles to be won. Tilea is the battleground from which these gold-hungry mercenaries will ply their expertise to all those willing to pay. Yet no matter the motivation, bold armies of Dogs of War depart every few weeks from the ports of Tilea and sail off into the sunset, ready to conqueror new lands and found new Kingdoms the likes of which no man have ever seen before.</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Each Mercenary Company charges its own rates, some straight forward and others are bizarre and unique. These Cost rates are flat and pay for exactly one mercenary&rsquo;s day of service. A full week of service is 3x the listed Cost for the mercenary, however they will not ask for a portion of any loot acquired. Time is money, and these elite mercenaries have no time for simple quick jobs and scuffles, they&rsquo;re above that. If you wish to hire an entire Unit of mercenaries, the Cost will be multiplied by 10x, however they will not share any additional Traits purchased. To make controlling a Unit easier, add the Swarm Creature Trait to the Unit for the purposes of combat. Optional Traits may be purchased for a single mercenary and increase the GC Cost of the mercenary by 50% of their base price per Trait and an increase in their share of the loot by a percentage equal to their Initial Fellowship Bonus prior to any Traits added. Only one mercenary may have the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.wGTD2LezlI6Atyy0]{Leader} Trait.</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> Availability is relative to the Empire and requires a d100 roll by the GM to see if they may be hired within the territory the PCs occupy. If the PCs wish to hire a company from outside of their territory, they must write a letter with half of the required payment to the designated mercenary company and wait. Their request will take 30 + d10 Days until the PC receives an answer, meanwhile it will take 30 &ndash; Fellowship Bonus Days for the mercenary, or mercenaries, to arrive should they accept any contract with the PC. The Availability of these mercenaries is increased by 2x when in the lands of Araby, Estalia, Marienburg, The Border Princes or Tilea.</p>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.DF6xOfImtDz0shIl]{Empire Veteran Mercenaries}</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 4 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 15% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 30% Chance (Does not increase outside The Empire)</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> The Empire</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> None</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.jL0A4uCEWKCbAswW]{Al Muktar&rsquo;s Desert Dogs}</h3>\n<p>Al Muktar's Desert Dogs are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that hail from the arid-deserts of great Araby. This band of bandit's and mercenaries are experienced raiders and skirmishers often raiding isolated villages, and caravans, while riding in calvary and wearing light armour or leather to make them agile in their attacks. Also, this Mercenary band is almost entirely composed of Arabyan corsairs or bandits from the inner deserts, where tribes of vicious warriors on camel-back raid the rich and fertile lands of Araby. This group however is lead by a foreigner, a man of the Empire, known as Werner Glook, a former son of a rich and aristocratic noblemen and merchant of the great City-State of Marienburg.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 5 GC + 2d10 Silver Shilling, 15% Portion of Loot or Jewelry</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Araby</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong><em>&nbsp;&ldquo;Mighty are the Muktarhin!&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.L3b24g2wiPlj27b5]{Bearmen of Urslo}</h3>\n<p><sup id=\"fn_2a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>The Bearmen, like many of the tribes of Norsca, are affected by the dark power of Chaos. This has made them as much beasts as men and all are touched with the mark of the were-bear to some extent, with shaggy hair, brutal ursine faces, massive teeth, and slashing claws. They wear barbaric clothing made of furs and held together with leather straps, and they have wild, unkempt hair. Their iron helmets have horns which make them look especially ferocious, and over their light chainmail armours, many wear long shaggy cloaks made from wild bears - often with the head or claws left on.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 5 GC + d10 Silver Shillings, +1 Corruption Point, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Norsca</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;The Dark Gods bless us!&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.2qZeAN3kSGuAea8O]{Birdmen of Catrazza}</h3>\n<p>The Birdmen of Catrazza are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that hail from the Tilean city-state of Verezzo. Wearing their trademark bird-mask, these Mercenaries are famous throughout the lands of Tilea for their ability to fly across the battlefield by using a pair of wings made entirely of canvas stretched out over a light wooden frame. This is strapped to their shoulders by means of a harness that leaves both hands free to shoot a smaller variant of the crossbow. In flight, the wings can be flapped by means of a stirrup attached to the feet, allowing the Birdmen to glide up and down the battlefield.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 5% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Verezzo, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Those magnificent men in their flying machines.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.buvf2sPJweZjfo8h]{Braganza's Besiegers}</h3>\n<p>Lead by Luca Braganza the Braganza's Besiegers are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that hails from the Tilean city-state of Miragliano, trained and maintained as heavily armored Crossbowmen. These veteran crossbowmen are typically equipped with thick plate Armour that protects the Besiegers from most harms, allowing them to fight against their foe's both in range and melee combat. The mercenary company uses a certain type of shield called a <em>Pavise</em>, which acts as a carriable shield either strapped into the Besiegers back, to protect the crossbowen while they reload, or stacked them up in a line to act as a make-shift barricade. The armour they wear is stylized in the exotic Miragliano style, with many wearing red-crested helmets. They have a strong rivalry with the Marksmen of Miragliano, both of whom are veteran crossbowmen mercenaries hailing from the same city.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Miragliano, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Invincibility at no extra charge.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.2KL05m7JNhLkTwDA]{Bronzino's Galloper Guns}</h3>\n<p>Al Muktar's Desert Dogs are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that hail from the arid-deserts of great Araby. This band of bandit's and mercenaries are experienced raiders and skirmishers often raiding isolated villages, and caravans, while riding in calvary and wearing light armour or leather to make them agile in their attacks. Also, this Mercenary band is almost entirely composed of Arabyan corsairs or bandits from the inner deserts, where tribes of vicious warriors on camel-back raid the rich and fertile lands of Araby. This group however is lead by a foreigner, a man of the Empire, known as Werner Glook, a former son of a rich and aristocratic noblemen and merchant of the great City-State of Marienburg.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 5 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, Gun Parts,15% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 5% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Remas, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;The biggest bang for your bucks!&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.7pw9N9kei2GaBCED]{Golgfag's Maneaters}</h3>\n<p>Golgfag's Maneaters also known as Golgfag's Ogres, are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries hailing from the arid mountains of the Ogre Kingdoms. This band of mercenaries consist entirely of Ogre Maneaters, lead by their leader and perhaps the most infamous Maneater alive, Golgfag Maneater. For as long as he had lived, Golfag Maneater has lead his brethren into countless battles for riches, glory, and most importantly, food. He has served in the armies of many warlords and generals of many nations, never discriminating on who he is fighting for or against.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>Such is his reputation in the battlefield that the Ogres under his command are never short on employment. This Ogre company has seen many exotic lands and horrific battlefields, forging these already formidable warriors into battle-hardened veterans, even among their fearsome kin.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 9 GC, Massive Feast, 25% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 5% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> The Ogre Kingdoms</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;You&rsquo;ve hired da rest, now try da best!&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.gQSGKfxKYvcwukNa]{Leopold&rsquo;s Leopard Company}</h3>\n<p>Leopold's Leopard Company is a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that has its origins within the great city-state of Luccini. The Leopard Company takes its name from the legendary Leopard of Luccini, which is a badge and mascot of the city. It is said that this Leopard was the guardian of the divine twins Lucan and Luccini, founders of the city. According to the story, the twins became lost in the wilderness &nbsp;when they were still only children and took refuge in a cave carved on a great&nbsp;rock, later to be the acropolis of the city. The cave was the lair of a leopard, but this was no ordinary leopard, she had two heads and three tails! She could also speak prophecies from one of her heads and warnings from the other.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>The Leopard protected the twins just as if they were her own cubs until shepherds found them. They also found the bones of many Orcs, wolves, bears and Trolls around the cave which the leopard had slain protecting the twins. According to the myth, the Leopard prophesied that Lucan and Luccina would found a great city on the rock and rule it as king and queen. Then the other head warned that the descendants of the twins would fight each other for the realm. After having thus spoken, the Leopard ventured deeper into the cave, and was never heard from again.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>The temple of Lucan and Luccina was built over the cave in which credulous people still believe the leopard lives. The guardians of the temple, hired by the priests and paid for by pious donations from the merchants of the city, were called the Leopard Company because their sworn duty was to guard the acropolis as ferociously as the leopard! Thus the regiment adopted the leopard as its badge.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Luccini, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Proceeds to the Luccini Temple&rsquo;s restoration fund.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.i91ZMpaViNL7IL20]{Long Drong Slayer Pirates}</h3>\n<p>Long Drong Slayer's Pirates (or Long Drong's Slayer Pirates<sup id=\"fn_2a_back\"></sup>&nbsp;are an infamous band of mercenary Sea Slayers that travel the seven seas aboard the <em>Fair Fregar</em>. They specialise in recovering lost pay chests - for the right price.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>Long Drong has a hook hand, peg leg, eyepatch, long red plaited beard, pistols stuffed down his breeches and a parrot on his shoulder which says 'bits o' gold, bits o' gold' all the time. His crew are a swarthy bunch of rogues who are proud to fight under the skulls and crossbones flag. All the pirates are festooned with pistols, which they shoot off in a hurricane of destruction. They carry so many pistols that they never need to reload.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 4 GC + 4d10 Brass Pennies, Several Kegs of Ale, 10% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Sartosa, Tilean Pirate Republic</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Lost pay chest recovery is our specialty.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.bnKYacPHTjUp2FIf]{Lumpin Croop&rsquo;s Fighting Cocks}</h3>\n<p>Lumpin Croop's Fighting Cocks are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that hail from the peaceful and agricultural farmlands of the Moot, the homeland of the Halfling race. Halflings are generally&nbsp;thought of as peaceful, well meaning, honest and sociable people, slow to anger and disdainful of violence. This, at least, is the common view, and it is a view readily encouraged by the sight of rosy cheeked, well-fed Halfling faces and broad Halfling smiles. Such are nature's gifts to that race, and the bountiful lands they occupy within the Empire of Man.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>However, even amongst this tolerant and easy-going people, there is the odd proverbial rotten apple that spoils an otherwise toothsome batch. In this case, the rotten apple goes by the name of Lumpin Croop and the batch in question is known as Lumpin Croop's Fighting Cocks. Extraordinary trackers and excellent marksmen, this band of Halfling game-wardens and hunters have fought many battles under Lumpins leadership, using their expert tracking skills to lead their allies through thick wilderness to ambush enemy armies without being notice.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>Lumpin Croop himself was a former thief and poacher before he became a mercenary, using his skills of stealth and tracking to mold the Fighting Cocks into what they are today. Ever since then, Lumpin has shown great compassion towards his fellow Halflings, staying up for hours to create an ingenious plan that would hopefully bring him and his company victory upon the battlefield.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 4 GC + d10 Silver, Meats &amp; Veggies, 15% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 20% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> The Moot, Empire Province</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Expert marksman, trackers and woodsmen. Baggage train guarding a specialty.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.MKSB5247qWhRtszn]{Marksmen of Miragliano}</h3>\n<p>The Marksmen of Miragliano are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries whoses origins hails from the Tilean city-state of Miragliano as their name implies. Although the use of the crossbow as a weapon of war is far from uncommon in Tilea, very few mercenary companies can hope to match the accuracy and precision of these marksmen. Captain Maximilian Damark, who is a veteran marksman with dozens of years of experience, currently leads the company.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>The crossbow has always been the favoured weapon in Tilea because its long range allows troops to shoot from high positions on the ramparts and across moats and ditches into the enemy hordes. Crossbow bolts are powerful enough to pierce armour and inflict mortal wounds on tough and determined opponents. The crossbow is also handy for use in confined spaces, like ramparts, towers, gateways, and the narrow strees of most Tilean cities and on board Tilean ships. It is therefore no surprise that the Tileans never really bothered with the use of ordinary bows.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Miragliano, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;We hit the right spot every time.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.Vt0eBKZYVPuQ5LM2]{Pirazzo&rsquo;s Lost Legion}</h3>\n<p>Pirazzo's Lost Legion<strong> </strong>are a famous band of&nbsp;Dogs of War mercenaries that had made legend for being one of the few armies in the world to have set foot upon the lush jungle-continent of Lustria, and live to tell the tale. Not only have these men survived this perilous journey, but their leader, Fernando Pirazzo himself became wealthy with the treasure he has gathered, and has since become a highly successful mercenary captain employed by the rich and wealthy of many nations of the Old World.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>It is said that his legion fought for the mysterious Lizardmen civilization of Lustria, aiding them in destroying a force of Undead warriors assailing the jungle nation from the eastern coast. His highly-effective fighting force devastated the Undead hordes, and managed to grab a ship and set sail for home with a large cargo of fabulous treasures. It is said that he became so wealthy that one of the Merchant Princes of Tilea tried to assassinate him in order to steal his wealth.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>Pirazzo's Lost Legion is all that remains of a expeditions sent to Lustria by the Merchants of Tobaro. The regiments in Tobaro were amongst the most reckless poverty-stricken youths of the city. The promise of untold wealth to be found in the jungles of Lustria was a temptation none could resist and they joined by the droves to be part of this magnificent expeditions. Although only one-third of these men will survive the journey, those that remain will become richer beyond their wildest dreams.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 10% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Tobaro, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Trained in Lustria.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.XZ6V7ELFSzn5Chhq]{Ricco's Republican Guard}</h3>\n<p>Ricco's Republican Guard are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries hailing from the great Republican city-state of Remas. The Republican Guard was raised in Remas by a rebellious group of merchants during the time of disastrous famines and widespread revolt that preceded the birth of the Republic. The regiment played a leading part in overthrowing the tyrannical Merchant Prince of Remas, the notorious Omilio Mondo. It was upon one of the Guard's pikes that Mondo's head was paraded around the city to the drunken applause of the mob.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>The revolt involved a great deal of vicious street fighting, in which no mercy was shown by either faction, and none asked for either. Several captains of the Republican Guard fell in quick succession, often shot in the back by Mondo's henchmen who had concealed themselves on the rooftops or high up in the bell towers surrounding the palace. In the thick of battle a common soldier named Ricco, known as Ragged Ricco because of his torn and bloodied clothing, assumed command. He seemed blessed by the war goddess herself and survived even the bloodiest hand-to-hand combat, despite fighting at the forefront of battle.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 5% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Remas, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Ricco&rsquo;s Republican Guard. The price of freedom!&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.2UTcCdtRYdYnMndf]{The Alcatani Fellowship}</h3>\n<p>The Alcatani Fellowship are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries that hail from the tranquil countryside of war-torn Tilea. The Alcatani Fellowship are unlike any other mercenary company in existence, for not only are they a crack and able fighting force but they also share a common heart for all commoners and peasants alike. As such, the Fellowship were considered the only mercenary company not completely driven by money, fighting also for the good-will of the people, making Rodrigo an extremely famous and popular mercenary captain amongst the common people.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 4 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 5% Portion of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 20% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Remas, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> &ldquo;The cut-price cut-throats you can afford!&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.tIObh1BrSEDV3ydw]{Vespero's Vendetta}</h3>\n<p>Vespero's Vendetta are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries which soon earned a notorious reputation as deadly duellists, reliable bodyguards, and expert saboteurs and assassins. The rivalry between the Merchant princes of Tilea are so violent that everyone of a right mind would hire bodyguards. These bodyguards would protect their master from plotters, assassins, and rebels alike. Inevitably however, bodyguards of rival families or houses would often clash with other families and small street duels are an often common place in the largest of Tilean cities.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>It is said that<strong> </strong>Stabbio the Bad, exiled Prince of Luccini, was the first to train his bodyguards as expert duellist, armed in what has since become the traditional duellist style. Others started copying his innovative style fighting after suffering at the hands of Stabbio's henchmen. A prince finding himself an exile or fugitive from his city is wise to hire a band of freelance duellist and use their services to regain or usurp power.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 7 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, 20% Portion of Loot or A Favor</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 5% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> Luccini, Tilean City-State</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Vengeance with a smile.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.FAwgnOLVWmd0faWD]{Voland's Venators}</h3>\n<p>Voland's Venators are a famous band of Dogs of War mercenaries whose reputation as the best cavalrymen in all of Tilea exceeds that of even veteran knights of the Empire or some say, even Bretonnia itself. These band of renegades, exiles, and disposed sons of nobles and lords are expert cavalrymen, and like everyone in the company, their leader is also a superb horsemen. The leader and captain of this expert band of knights is named Voland. No one knows of Voland's origin, but some say he was the son of a noblemen of the Empire, or the disposed son of an Elector Count, and some would even say that he is none other then the bastard son of the Emperor himself. Voland himself neither denies nor acknowledges these rumours.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p>Voland came to Tilea from somewhere within the Empire. At the time he was just one of many mercenary heroes hired by the Tileans in the never-ending civil wars that ravaged the land. He rose to prominence as leader of a band of mercenary knights called the Venators, which means \"Hunters\" in low Tilean. The motives of Voland and his brother knights could not have been more different from the Bretonnian or even the Empire traditions of Knighthood. They were soldiers of fortune interested only in two things, namely money and spending it. They were also expert cavalry whose thunderous charge could scatter the deepest enemy formations - something which the Tileans desperately needed, but lacked until that time.<sup id=\"fn_1a_back\"></sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>- Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 6 GC + 5d10 Silver Shillings, Barrel of Wine or Ale, 20% of Loot</p>\n<p><strong>Availability:</strong> 5% Chance</p>\n<p><strong>Nation of Origin:</strong> The Empire</p>\n<p><strong>Motto:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Voland&rsquo;s Venators. The answer. No questions asked.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Kislev Bestiary</h2>\n<p>Standing at the very doorsteps of madness and corruption, the nation of Kislev has been, since its founding, a nation driven by warfare. Throughout the course of human history, Kislev has always bred hardy people, not only because of the harsh climate and generally infertile lands, but also due to the constant depredation by the raiders of the Northern Waste. The fiery hatred for these Men of the North is well evident, for so many years have the sons of Kislev died by their hands, with the Ungol tribes of the north bearing the greatest of this hatred. Since the founding of this mighty kingdom, Kislev has been, since its very creation, under siege by the murderous Hordes of Chaos Undivided, a kingdom that sits forever at the brink of total annihilation. Countless generations of Kislevites have fought, bled, and died in the snowy tundra of those harsh northern lands, and it is thanks to these brave Kislevite warriors that the Kingdoms of Men have managed to flourish in the south, huddled together in their warm and safe homes, whilst the Sons of Kislev fight till they draw their last dying breath.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.hZOCxG0RQIYnpWrh]{Horse Archer}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.gZEDWIJk7AIPpIiB]{Kossar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.QjlSBSVA8rz7YXan]{Streltsi}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.ZXets547HhnAfOSj]{Streltsi Captain}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.IktbmeE5aTSNJdWB]{Winged Lancer}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.CMH0LCfr7UKJCRH8]{Gryphon Legion}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.GhlGEjwZpfHT37aZ]{Chekist}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.1zWor5sp4AgF85bi]{Silovik}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.dKl8bS4FV0DN40Mz]{Kreml Guard}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.QyG94Nh1prfMER4p]{Boyar}</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.1qQZhMWwNcyODfW4"}}}
{"_id":"61csp8sWiQWkRdsT","name":"Divine Lore of Araby","content":"<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Ormazd</h2>\n<p>Although its roots go back further, scholars typically date the creation of the Cult of the Great Prophet to the 11th century IC, making it among the youngest of the major human religions. The Cult of the Great Prophet started in his home city of Martek, the birthplace of modern Arabyan Civilization, during the time of the prophet Mulhaed al-Quyat&rsquo;s life. He began receiving what Arabyans regard as divine revelations delivered through the god Ormazd. Afterwards he was said to have spawned the oasis&rsquo; across Araby, granting fertile land and precious water to the people. Since the &ldquo;War of the Death&rdquo; and the destruction of Bel-Aliad at the hands of Arkhan the Black more than a thousand years prior, Araby had been a broken nation, but Mulhaed al-Quyat reunited the peoples of Araby, and through faith became the first Great Sultan. Today, despite Araby&rsquo;s decline after the Crusades in the 15th Century IC, the faith is held strongly. However, it is theorized by imperial scholars that the entity the Great Prophet received visions from was an even older god, perhaps one that was worshipped by another now long-lost civilization.</p>\n<p>His holy symbol is that of a crescent moon, and it can be seen on many Arabyan standards, and even the shape of their shield; something that his worshippers believe will bless them in battle.</p>\n<h3><strong>Ormazd's Blessings and Strictures :</strong></h3>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.ElmLfnrXliStS9CP]{Battle}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.Cg2Q3TV66cpmheHS]{Courage}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.52846%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.maUl7MoLvuvTOhM0]{Grace}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 23.6365%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.K5DE9cceinUTIrem]{Protection}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.815%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.GvaOlWY8iD5CO1WB]{Tenacity}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.FRkIz2sR7ZC92W2G]{Wisdom}</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li>There are no gods equal to Ormazd.</li>\n<li>Pray facing Martek three times each day to Ormazd: at dawn, two hours past midday, and two hours past sunset.</li>\n<li>Donate a fixed portion of your income to believers in need. Many rulers and wealthy Arabyans build temples, drinking fountains, hospitals, schools, and other institutions both as a religious duty and to secure the blessings associated with charity.</li>\n<li>During the daylight hours of the ninth month of the Imperial Calendar, all healthy adult Arabyan believers are required to abstain from food and drink. Through this temporary deprivation, they renew their awareness of and gratitude for everything the Great Prophet has provided in their lives.</li>\n<li>Every Arabyan believer whose health and finances permit it must make at least one visit to the holy city of Martek per year.</li>\n<li>Vanquish all undead&mdash;in memory of Bel-Aliad.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Miracles of Ormazd</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.ImMCUkXCD5F7fQbC]{Burning Sands}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.DojGXBk7cdj7RGWx]{Bury the Soul}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.ZVVhCsOF2aVlcgNn]{Forgiveness of Al-Alnon}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.PWHhC2ftAjNqaLEr]{Healing Sands}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.ry0e2Ouk1R3AGN05]{Sword of Ormazd}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.SIj5lIpHOhM32Ab1]{Waters of Life}</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.mh2lRoNuI01Tn2nM"}}}
{"_id":"AkPUknDtzejb1LdK","name":"Divine Lore of Ind","content":"<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">The Devas of Ind</h2>\n<p>Ind is a land of many mysteries, but little is more mysterious and unique as its religion. The Kingdoms of Ind is also widely known as the Land of a Thousand Gods, and for good reason. The piety on display&mdash;from the temples of marble that reach the sky to the innumerable symbols found in every household, piece of clothing and jewelry&mdash;is enough to raise an eyebrow from all but the most dogmatic of the Sigmarite, Myrmidian and Ulrician faiths. The Indan religion is one of polytheism, worshipping not one but numerous gods (or &lsquo;Devas&rsquo; as the people of Ind call them) at once, each representing a different aspect of the religion&rsquo;s teachings. While the idea of practicing the faith of multiple gods isn&rsquo;t new, it&rsquo;s the equal worship of the Divine Trinity (Brahmir, Vaishna and Shaivi) and their children that makes them unique. Unlike the Empire that squabbles between its own faiths--such as the Cult of Sigmar and Ulric--the people of Ind worship under a unified pantheon. Some gods fall into greater favor than others, but it is extremely rare to find sects dedicated to only one or a few gods and excluding the rest of the pantheon.</p>\n<p>Priests of the Divine Trinity can be found wearing long, colorful robes with markings on their foreheads. They are known to be kind and understanding individuals, wise men and women highly educated and sought after for advice. Their war priests are a different beast altogether: War Priests of Ind are said to be giants of men and women, avatars of their gods sent to punish the wicked and purge Ind of corruption. They are clad in armor and wear massive turbans called dastaar which are covered in religious symbols of the various gods and are said to grow larger as the war priest gains experience. Some dastaar can weight up to 50 kg from the sheer amount of charms and trophies of war placed in them.</p>\n<h3><strong>Devas' Blessings and Strictures :</strong></h3>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.ElmLfnrXliStS9CP]{Battle}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.iIfYOlNrLb0uiV8c]{Fortune}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.52846%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.C92dpJPRYpkZFsGu]{Healing}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 23.6365%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.K5DE9cceinUTIrem]{Protection}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.815%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.Jkt465WPdRcejLwl]{Recuperation}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.prayers.tMocig1z9dHKNiCT]{Wit}</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Brahmir, the Deva of Creation:</strong> Do not harm cows as they represent life given from the Devas. They are a source of goodness and its milk nourishes all creatures.</li>\n<li><strong>Vaishna, the Deva of Preservation:</strong> Protect your lands, people and family at all cost. Do not allow the corruption of the Dark Ones to poison the minds of the innocent.</li>\n<li><strong>Shaivi, the Deva of Destruction:</strong> Seek out and destroy the chaos of the world: the Greenskins, the Heathens, the Ratmen and Dark Ones--all must burn so creation may flow.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Miracles of the Devas</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.86KwePa9mrNUpnYo]{Avatar of Vaishna}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.6rMjBOL0gqCyRJwg]{Banish the Wicked}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.7KHR1brNKrHI6Eke]{Brahmir's Gift}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.azziHRjEfq2BBMgQ]{Dance of Flame}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.suQ5zQyJgjmyebrd]{Gilgadresh&rsquo;s Fortune}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.1WkkjP6ZdQCKbm66]{Idran&rsquo;s Will}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.UpH0IDRjwbeInvnG]{Sweat of Creation}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.prayers-nom.zmsm6fDykgIn4ufl]{Trident of Shaivi}</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.RzEiKarE8h5u2uP7"}}}
{"_id":"B08VRo2SPReubqXi","name":"Knight of Bretonnia Rules","content":"<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">A True Knight of Bretonnia</h2>\n<h3>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careerentries-nom.402NAYsjvpKm30nW]{Knight of the Realm}</h3>\n<h3><strong>Blessings of the Lady :</strong></h3>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.prayers\" data-id=\"ElmLfnrXliStS9CP\"> Battle</a></td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.prayers\" data-id=\"Cg2Q3TV66cpmheHS\"> Courage</a></td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.52846%; text-align: center;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.prayers\" data-id=\"iIfYOlNrLb0uiV8c\"> Fortune</a></td>\n<td style=\"width: 23.6365%; text-align: center;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.prayers\" data-id=\"KSDrXcieyRc37YI7\"> Might</a></td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.815%; text-align: center;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.prayers\" data-id=\"K5DE9cceinUTIrem\"> Protection</a></td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.66%; text-align: center;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.prayers\" data-id=\"2WN0muIB2BFd4kBO\"> Righteousness</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3><strong>Seven Commandments</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>To serve the Lady of the Lake.</li>\n<li>To defend the domains entrusted to them.</li>\n<li>To protect the weak and fight for the right.</li>\n<li>Always to fight the enemies of virtue and order.</li>\n<li>Never to give up the fight until the foe be defeated.</li>\n<li>Never to break faith with a friend or ally.</li>\n<li>Always to display honor and courtesy.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Rules of Honor</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A knight may only fight hand-to-hand, with sword or lance; they may not use a missile weapon.</li>\n<li>A knight shall always accept a challenge towards personal combat.</li>\n<li>A knight shall not draw sword against their fellow Bretonnian knights, except in trial by combat or within a tournament.</li>\n<li>A knight shall not allow themselves to be captured alive.</li>\n<li>A knight shall not flee from the enemy, nor retreat without proper tactical cause.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Knightly Virtues</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.AOguCWo0euajXABc]{Virtue of Audacity}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.GvrD3PdtxOygwrNl]{Virtue of Confidence}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.0uaPQY15ZnjF5ZzV]{Virtue of Discipline}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.46Xib40e7vfyll1c]{Virtue of Duty}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.kAxoOlRY7PJL48l5]{Virtue of Empathy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.YtIMTxLyMNhk3ods]{Virtue of Heroism}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.SypwNmrxyYPfk8Fd]{Virtue of Noble Disdain}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.zZ0UU4sxnyz6Smf0]{Virtue of Purity}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.oKr9BnSc6lJHmtQO]{Virtue of Stoicism}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.LHmsgZcq55OSWamY]{Virtue of the Ideal}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.q7aSRxEixg00EpE1]{Virtue of the Impetuous Knight}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.u6bBYqjEoKU1b2wo]{Virtue of the Joust}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.KgEVJODvpRJEQpVK]{Virtue of the Knightly Temper}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.Gy4NuuXPt2XE8E3B]{Virtue of the Penitent}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Becoming a Questing Knight</h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.k3H9GpfaIxdyZt4m]{Virtue of the Quest} :&nbsp;</strong>This Talent has several effects, but they only apply whilst the character is in the career of the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight}. If they complete the career and move on or abandon it to take up a different basic career, the effects of the Talent lapse. If the character completes the career and becomes a @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.cAwJfiBBQvnftP8F]{Grail Knight}, the Talent is lost altogether. If they simply abandoned the Quest, they retain the Talent receiving endless visions, and if the knight re-enters the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} career its effects apply once more.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Becoming a Grail Knight</h2>\n<p><strong>The Grail Quest:</strong> The @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight's} quest is a defining feature of the how the character plays each session, both mechanically and during roleplaying. It must provide a sufficient challenge in order for the knight to logically complete the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} career and to enter the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.cAwJfiBBQvnftP8F]{Grail Knight} career, and the adventures included should have more significance than the defeat of random fringe bands of bandits, greenskins or a monster. Once the character has reached the point of advancement from @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} to @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.cAwJfiBBQvnftP8F]{Grail Knight}, they should be put under one last significant task by The Lady, usually consisting of 3-5 or more sessions of story content leading to their final encounter with The Green Knight.</p>\n<p><strong>Significance : </strong>There are many different types of significance which suit different styles of play. In one example, the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} could unearth and defeat a significant threat to the land of Bretonnia be it internal or outside its borders:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>For example: </strong>This might be a secretive underground Chaos or Necromancy cult hiding in a major city or large town, an Orc warlord ravaging the local populace--possibly the beginning of an Orc WAAAGH!!!, a Bestigor gathering a war herd, or even a Norscan raiding party being led by a potential Chosen of the Chaos Gods unleashing carnage in their names.</p>\n<p>Another method could have the events of the quest force the Questing Knight to face their weaknesses or past mistakes. Thus, a knight who failed to defend a village against an Orc attack might find themselves placed to defend a different village from a horde of Beastmen. On the other hand, a knight with a tendency to lose their temper might find themselves forced to calmly negotiate peace between two nobles or warring factions who hate each other and have nothing but contempt for the Questing Knight and their companions.</p>\n<p>Whilst other player characters may be involved, they are essentially following the knight on their quest. If the Questing Knight is uncovering a major threat to the land, then it&rsquo;s the sort of thing adventurers do anyway. If they&rsquo;re facing their own flaws, the other characters may feel a bit left out, so considering bridging the knight&rsquo;s personal journey with one or more of their companions. Perhaps the knight failed to protect one of them in a past encounter causing them to lose an eye or an arm, or gain a Corruption Point? The best thing to do here is talk to the players and see what they would be happiest doing.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>The Green Knight</h2>\n<p>The final part of the quest, the confrontation with the Green Knight, is for the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} alone. The combat with the Green Knight could be a purely symbolic gesture if the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} has saved Bretonnia from a major threat, or it could be a test of whether or not the knight has the skill to back up their acts of chivalry. At this point it is up to the GM how to proceed. The Green Knight is one of, if not the most skilled duelist in Warhammer Fantasy, besting innumerable foes and being virtually immortal; however, his stats don&rsquo;t need to reflect this fact. The Green Knight is a test, just like any of the tests sent by The Lady to her loyal knights during the rest of their Quest. It is recommended, if you stat the Green Knight, that he acts as a counter to the knight PC, with his Characteristics, Trappings and Talents being nearly identical. Once the duel is finished (preferably in victory) the final step with the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.cAwJfiBBQvnftP8F]{Grail Knight} is all that remains.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>The Lady of the Lake</h2>\n<p>The meeting with the Lady is a dramatic event. Lights shine from the lake that you meet her by. The Lady, dazzlingly beautiful, walks across water and through the mists holding the Grail for the knight to drink, and as the character drinks from the Grail they see the whole world in a new divine way. The @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} hears the stories of the encounters between the greatest of Bretonnia&rsquo;s heroes, including the Grail Companions, and the Green Knight and the Lady. Their encounters include elements from the stories made from the experiences of the @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.ajuoEMh4XZ5SFSyI]{Questing Knight} and the party they accompany, making it clear that the knight&rsquo;s journey and friendship is just as much a part of the same tradition since Bretonnia&rsquo;s unification. After this ceremony is concluded, the PC may select a Grail Virtue, assuming they have purchased at least one Knightly Virtue.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Grail Virtues</strong></h3>\n<p>You may select one Grail Virtue after advancing to @Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.careers-nom.cAwJfiBBQvnftP8F]{Grail Knight}. This virtue cannot be retracted or upgraded and requires you&rsquo;ve acquired the Knightly Virtue of the same name: You cannot acquire the Grail Virtue of Audacity for instance without first acquiring the Knightly Virtue of Audacity. You gain a permanent +5 bonus to your Strength and Toughness Characteristics this does not count towards your Advances; moreover, you gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.SfUUdOGjdYpr3KSR]{Regenerate} Trait and the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.3wCtgMDNnu8MFmyk]{Immunity&nbsp;(Corruption, Disease, Fatigue, Poison)} Trait.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.xTmXkYnDt76NB49D]{Grail Virtue of Audacity}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.brXOeqIBAoxQyXBF]{Grail Virtue of Confidence}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.TanGz1CH6Ub2mWyB]{Grail Virtue of Discipline}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.1uZTdPW6lk2pzWLa]{Grail Virtue of Duty}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.nPnQjIR87psLH7Rw]{Grail Virtue of Empathy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.E600zEb7jFqzQjC4]{Grail Virtue of Heroism}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.kAlDxoURoY1EnQTo]{Grail Virtue of Knightly Temper}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.LBCZ5g5IJiPorGb9]{Grail Virtue of Noble Disdain}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.CM9Iy8UlvV8e9vfN]{Grail Virtue of Purity}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.JEEeQ8DF9gyRISM4]{Grail Virtue of Stoicism}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.sSQqfayNttWiw4lF]{Grail Virtue of the Ideal (Strength)}&nbsp;<em>or&nbsp;</em>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.1OQAmuGFmGKifiOt]{Grail Virtue of the Ideal (Toughness)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.zaKBWFzWCXDVk9Co]{Grail Virtue of the Impetuous Knight}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.BqJ6Fmc9oRn85k9d]{Grail Virtue of the Joust}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.talents-nom.7j5SaKqq4isvMX6T]{Grail Virtue of the Penitent}</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.qm0Bw49k6qzrXItY"}}}
{"_id":"FPxoZ6ZAz1PumE1k","name":"Lore of the Desert","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.jdnd8sOb6vCkOvS5"}},"content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Lore of the Desert</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Lore of the Desert is the dominant form of magic within Araby, with its Magicians held in high regard within its social class. The Lore of the Desert is considered a difficult Wind to perceive and manipulate, appearing scattered even to those skilled with the Sight, resembling a chaotic sandstorm as it swirls around them. This makes it tricky to manipulate but dangerous in the hands of a skilled Magician. The wind is associated with power, intelligence, and prestige. The Magicians of Araby are acclaimed for their skill, knowledge, and their sheer determination, even able to bend the wills of the Djinn, magical being of the elements, to their service. Spells from the Lore of the desert are some of the most bizarre, including summoning desert sands even in areas of the world where it impossible, and those that summon Djinn to the mortal plane. There are also more manipulative applications used to fool enemies by summoning mirror images of their deepest desires, such as piles of gold, or even copies of yourself making it impossible for them to confront you. Magicians of the Lore of the Desert tend to wear fine silk robes known as &ldquo;thawbs&rdquo; in Araby accompanied by a traditional headwrap known as a &ldquo;keffiyeh&rdquo;. Due to their higher status within the Arabyan hierarchy, Magicians rarely dress the same--dying their robes in exotic colors and having them designed with eccentric and unique patterns that reflect their personality, favoring fashion over practicality. Those with the money to do so flaunt their wealth with glittering jewelry hanging from their necks, and fine bangles and rings across their arms and fingers.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore Attribute:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong>&nbsp;Magicians of the Lore of the Desert use many artefacts associated with the harsh arid lands of Araby, supplemented by crystals, glass jars, gemstones, lamps and small statues depicting the mystical beings known as Djinn. White candles, silver carvings, and bleached paper are also common.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Spells:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.7puMQv0T8uM1JNlB]{Curse of the Djinn}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.FX7LgkoFvUgp5FZc]{Dancing Scimitar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.3x11TmfrdUNvRkgr]{Flying Servant}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.kHqr2B7GahN31JCz]{Mirage}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.oF0GbqL8w3W49Jus]{Quicksand}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.Vd1LiC1lzs5JkptN]{Sand Blast}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.HBcnXlSkCmfpZ7GY]{Sandstorm}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.XxmlmN89d5RT012Y]{Summon Djinn}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.spells-nom.lNZX4QYOOBynrt6g]{Sun Spear}</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"Gfsvh1l6Npt3OPWK","name":"Regiments of the Empire","content":"<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Regiments of the Empire</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;By decree of Magnus the Pious, every province and city-state in the Empire of Man must maintain a State or Provincial Army at its own expense. Together, these regional forces make up the Imperial Army, the force that mans the Empire's fortresses, patrols the Empire's borders, repels the Empire's invaders, and, in many places, acts as local law-enforcement. These soldiers are armed with a variety of weapons, the most common being the Halberd, Sword, and Spear.</p>\n<p>Since its existence, the Empire of Man has always been a nation born and bred for war, fighting off foes uncountable with the will, the steel, and the faith of their patriotic citizenry. With an unending chain of constant warfare, the armies of the Empire are brimmed with grizzled Veterans of many campaigns, each one lead by an even greater man of strength, valor and heroic leaderships. As their nation progress throughout the centuries, innovations and inventions were re-engineered for the use of warfare, with the armies of the Empire now stockpiled with large quantities of devastating black-powder weaponry and the technological marvels of the 25th century.&rdquo; <strong>&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Through centuries of blood and war, each province has perfected its own unique forms of warfare, each with regiments of renown specializing in different weaponry, tactics and cultures. They are shaped just as much by the heraldry and traditions of their home province as they are by the grim realities of war. While the Empire is a unified force of man and order against the dangers of Chaos, it is its many parts, from Reikland to Ostland, spread across its many provinces that gives it its true edge. It&rsquo;s its military reflects that quality the most.</p>\n<p>These bonuses are granted to those who select the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.kT0ZI0LoHmIvhjPk]{Soldier} Career in the <a title=\"WFRP 4E Core Module\" href=\"https://foundryvtt.com/packages/wfrp4e-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WFRP 4E Core Module</a> and dedicate themselves to a specific province of the Empire. The bonuses increase as the Soldier PC progresses in their career, starting from Recruit to Officer. Please consult the GM before making any homebrew modifications towards your character. Your character must originate from the Empire and their respective Province, with the exception of Marienburg, to qualify for these Regimental bonuses.</p>\n<p>All Lore Skills and Talents granted to the soldier by their Regiment are treated as if added to their Career and may be purchased and advanced as normal. If you leave your Regiment under any conditions, such as being discharged or changing Careers, you maintain all additional Skills and Talent advances; however, you will not be eligible to join or maintain employment with any special unit in the Regiments of Renown section, with the exception of Marienburg who hires anyone.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Altdorf</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Averland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Hochland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Marienburg</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Middenland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Nordland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Nuln</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Ostermark</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Ostland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Reikland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Stirland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Talabecland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Talabheim</strong></h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h3><strong>Wissenland</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>1. Altdorf</h2>\n<p><strong>Recruit:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Reikland)}</p>\n<p><strong>Soldier:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.AcnFuDKRemLI9ey7]{Nose for Trouble} Talent</p>\n<p><strong>Sergeant: </strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Sigmar)} Skill</p>\n<p><strong>Officer:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.b4x1qEWcevX7xK58]{Schemer} Talent</p>\n<p><strong>Uniform Colors:&nbsp;</strong>Red and Blue</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>2. Averland</h2>\n<p><strong>Recruit:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Averland)}</p>\n<p><strong>Soldier:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Dwarfs)} Talent</p>\n<p><strong>Sergeant:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Dwarfs)}&nbsp;<em>or&nbsp;</em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Greenskins )} Skill</p>\n<p><strong>Officer:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.tXKX29QZBdHmyMc7]{Combat Reflexes} Talent</p>\n<p><strong>Uniform Colors:&nbsp;</strong>Yellow and Black</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>3. Hochland</h2>\n<p><strong>Recruit:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Hochland)}</p>\n<p><strong>Soldier:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.jrYW2OyDHd1Md2my]{Sharpshooter} Talent</p>\n<p><strong>Sergeant:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Blackpowder)} Skill</p>\n<p><strong>Officer:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.cygaI9gq4BQJvbB5]{Sniper} Talent</p>\n<p><strong>Uniform Colors:&nbsp;</strong>Red and Green</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>4. Marienburg</h2>\n<p><strong>Recruit:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Westerland)}</p>\n<p><strong>Soldier:&nbsp;</strong>You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Guilders)} Talent</p>\n<p><stro